        {
          "text": "The name is derived from the letter 半 (han) meaning \"half\" and 蔵 (zō/zou) meaning \"to hide\"."
        },
        {
          "text": "According to Japanese mythology, Ame no Habakiri is one of the 4 Totsuka swords. Ame no Habakiri was wielded by Susanoo to slay Yamata no Orochi.",
